<recipe>
    <name>Philly Cheese Steak by Bobby Flay</name>
    <indexCharacter>P</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>4</servings>
    <instructions>Place steak in freezer for 30 to 45 minutes; this makes it easier to slice the meat. Remove the meat from the freezer and slice very thinly. Heat griddle or grill pan over high heat. Brush steak slices with oil and season with salt and pepper. Cook for 45 to 60 seconds per side. Place several slices of the meat on the bottom half of the roll, spoon some of the cheese sauce over the meat, and top with the mushrooms, onions, and peppers.</instructions>
